Aley Green Brinley was born 15 August 1885 in Harold, Wieborger Co., Texas FootNote(WWI draft registration, WWII draft registration, CA Death Index Summary) to William R. and Matilda J. (Atteberry) Brinley. He married Gertrude Frances Weber (27 September 188514 March 1961 FootNote(CA Death Index Summary) July 1916 in Winters and had two children Betty Ann Brinley, who died young, and John W. Brinley John Weber Brinley.

He was a station agent for the Southern Pacific Railroad, and was honored in Davis by having the A.G. Brinley Plaza and the A. G. Brinley Award named after him.
